    "en": {
      "title": "No one can lower the inflation for the next 6 months",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Central Bank Governor Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe says that no one can bring inflation below 30% to 40% in the next 6 months, and the economy is expected to contract more than any year in history.",
        "Commenting on the restriction of economic activities in the country, the Governor of the Central Bank, Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe, expressed his views in a forum organized by the Sri Lanka Press Club (Press Club). The Governor who further commented,",
        "\"Within the next 3-6 months, there will be only limited economic activity in this country, which means the economy will contract. We expect that this year the economy will contract by more than any year in history. Inflation will be 30% to 40% for everyone in the next 6 months. It cannot be brought lower. This is the problem that affects the poor and vulnerable people. Especially if the government does not provide support, it will be difficult for the poor people with low income to live on their income. You will see the poverty levels in this country increasing. More people will fall below the poverty level. When the economy shrinks, we will see more people losing their jobs because small and medium scale industries will not be able to run normally.\" said."
      ],
